node.text:
SAS colleagues are joining forces to provide health care across Stockholm and some of our amazing cabin crew put this film together, showing how they go from ready for takeoff to ready to take action.
. 
If you want to see more of their work, their challenges and moments of joy, check out @coronaexpress08. They are truly inspirational, showing relentless determination to help out where it is needed the most.
. 
We are so proud of your work and hope to have you back in the air again soon.
. 
#flysas #TravelersTakeAction

node.text:
Due to the coronavirus and the measures implemented by national authorities, the demand for air travel is essentially non-existent. SAS has therefore decided to put most of its operations on hold, starting Monday March 16 and until necessary prerequisites for commercial air traffic returns. 
To support our customers, we will in the next few days do our utmost to uphold a certain level of operation to enable travelers to return from their destinations.
Information regarding the traffic situation and specific flights will be constantly updated on our website.

The waiting time at our call centers is extraordinary long. We kindly ask that you only call us if your flight departs within the next 3 days.

node.title: SAS CEO Rickard Gustafson informs about the current situation

node.text:
Due to the Coronavirus and the measures implemented by national authorities, the demand for air travel is essentially nonexistent. SAS has therefore decided to put most of its operations on hold, starting Monday March 16 and until necessary prerequisites for commercial air traffic returns. 
To support our customers, we will in the next few days do our outmost to uphold a certain level of operation to enable travelers to return to their destinations. 
Information regarding the traffic situation and specific flights will be constantly updated on our website - https://sas.travel/en/trafficinfo 
The waiting time at our call centers are extraordinarily long. We kindly ask that you only call us if your flight departs within the next 3 days.

Due to the coronavirus and the measures implemented by national authorities, the demand for air travel is essentially non-existent. SAS has therefore decided to put most of its operations on hold, starting Monday March 16 and until necessary prerequisites for commercial air traffic returns. 
To support our customers, we will in the next few days do our utmost to uphold a certain level of operation to enable travelers to return from their destinations.

Information regarding the traffic situation and specific flights will be constantly updated on our website.

The waiting time at our call centers is extraordinary long. We kindly ask that you only call us if your flight departs within the next 3 days.

Please not that we will not be answering any questions in this forum. We urge to visit flysas.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SAS - Scandinavian Airlines on August 06, 2021. May be an image of airplane and outdoors.

node.text:
Welcome home Olympians! 🇩🇰🇳🇴🇸🇪

Earlier today, SK984 arrived in Copenhagen from Tokyo. Onboard the flight were several Olympic medal winners - which we celebrated with a water salute, together with @copenhagenairport.

We at SAS are thrilled to be proud carrier of the Scandinavian Olympic athletes! Join us in congratulating them with their impressive results!

#flysas #wearetravelers #japan #tokyo

Photo by @copenhagenairport.

node.text:
New routes to the Canary Islands✈️

With stunning diverse landscape and fabulous beaches, the Canary Islands have much to offer. They offer rich culture, a great food scene and countless opportunities for hiking and outdoor adventures. Our new routes from Stockholm and Gothenburg will be a great addition to our routes to the islands from Copenhagen and Oslo.

#flysas #wearetravelers #canaryislands

node.text:
Travelers for 75 years 🇩🇰🇳🇴🇸🇪

August 1st marks our 75th anniversary as the proud carrier of travelers to, from and within Scandinavia. And while a lot has happened since our first-ever flight from Stockholm to New York 75 years ago, we’re even more excited about what has yet to come.

Thank you, for traveling with us for all these years! We are looking forward to welcoming you on board our flights today, tomorrow and for many more years to come.

#flysas #SAS75 #wearetravelers

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SAS - Scandinavian Airlines in Pula, Croatia. May be an image of ocean, twilight, sky and nature.

node.text:
Travelers explore Pula 🇭🇷

Rising above the Adriatic Sea on the southern tip of the peninsula is Pula. Besides being home to one of the world's best preserved Roman amphitheaters, Pula is also known for its unbroken blue coastal line, amazing beaches, great restaurants and its relaxed Mediterranean atmosphere. 

Fly direct to Pula from Copenhagen, Stockholm and Oslo this summer. We’ll get you there safely.

#flysas #wearetravelers #croatia #pula

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SAS - Scandinavian Airlines on July 12, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and indoor.

node.text:
Scandinavia is rooting for you! 🇩🇰🇳🇴🇸🇪

We are thrilled to be proud carrier of the Scandinavian Olympic athletes! Today, the second flight bound for the Summer Games left Oslo. With a quick pit-stop in Copenhagen, to pick up fellow Scandinavian athletes, the flight is now safely on its way to Fukuoka in Japan.

The athletes will be traveling on one of our brand-new A350’s, which is one of the most fuel-efficient aircraft in the industry and our fleet’s latest pride and joy.

Join us in wishing the athletes all the best of luck at this year’s games!

#flysas #wearetravelers #japan #tokyo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SAS - Scandinavian Airlines on July 10, 2021. May be an image of 8 people, people standing and text that says 'Scandinavian'.

node.text:
Cheering for the Scandinavian athletes! 🇩🇰🇳🇴🇸🇪

Today, this amazing crew made sure that the Scandinavian Olympic athletes had the best possible start. The first athletes departed from Copenhagen, to join the Summer Olympic Games in Tokyo – on our first flight back to Haneda airport.

We are thrilled to be proud carrier of the Scandinavian Olympic athletes, getting them safely and comfortably to Tokyo.

Join us in wishing them all the best of luck at this year’s games!

#flysas #wearetravelers #japan #tokyo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SAS - Scandinavian Airlines in Naples, Italy. May be an image of sky.

node.text:
Who doesn’t like pizza? 🇮🇹

The city of Naples boasts 1,500 pizzerias and la Pizza Napoletana joined the Unesco World Heritage List in 2017. In addition to great food, Italy’s third largest city offers authentic Italian vibes and some of Europe’s finest beaches near the Gulf of Naples.

Naples is a must-visit destination for pizza lovers and everyone who wants to enjoy the Italian summer. We’ll get you to Naples safely.

#flysas #wearetravelers #italy #naples

node.accessibility_caption: The island of Sicily in Italy.

node.text:
Let’s take a trip to Sicily 🇮🇹

It’s been called the perfect place to relax, and a spot that will stay with you long after you leave. The island in the Mediterranean Sea offers great experiences, an amazing food scene and, not to forget, the famous Sicilian granita.

Explore Sicily this summer with SAS. We offer direct flights to both Palermo on the Northern coast and Catania on the Eastern cost. No matter which destination you choose, we’ll get you there safely.

#flysas #wearetravelers #italy #sicily #palermo #catania

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SAS - Scandinavian Airlines in United States. May be an image of airplane, indoor and text that says 'SAS BUSINESS ted SAS Get started'.

node.text:
Happy 4th of July! 🇺🇸

In celebration of Independence Day, we’ve set the mood lights to red, white and blue on some of our flights bound for the US. All of us at SAS wishes you all the best of festivities, and are looking forward to visit the US soon!

Photo by SAS Purser @madsguldagerphotography.

#flysas #wearetravelers #fourthofjuly

Happy midsummer, travelers!🌸

All of us at SAS wish you the best of celebrations, and that you get as little rain and as much joy as possible!☀️💙

#flysas #wearetravelers #midsummer

node.text:
Barcelona is ready for you 💙

Barcelona, the city where urban life meets the easygoing vibes of the Mediterranean, offer both famous sights like the Sagrada Família – as well as small tapas bars and streets filled with whimsical, colorful architecture.

Read more about the local restrictions and our traffic program here:
https://sas.travel/go/travelready

node.text:
A timeless Mediterranean haven💙

A destination that truly is a classic is the Balearian island of Mallorca. Flying into Palma, travelers can explore the countless turquoise bays around the island during daytime and then relish the vibe of Palma after a long day in the sun. 

Read more about the local restrictions and our traffic program here: https://sas.travel/go/travelready

#flysas #wearetravelers #palma #mallorca #spain #travelinspiration
